    <item>
      <title>Administration: GitHub</title>
      <link>https://go-vela.github.io/docs/administration/server/docker/github/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://go-vela.github.io/docs/administration/server/docker/github/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;h2 id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This section provides all required dependencies to install and start the server with Docker that connects to GitHub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;dependency-1-docker&#34;&gt;Dependency 1: Docker&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docker.com/&#34;&gt;Docker&lt;/a&gt; will be used for downloading the server and managing the lifecycle of the application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can refer to &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/&#34;&gt;Docker&amp;rsquo;s official documentation&lt;/a&gt; on installing and configuring the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;dependency-2-redis&#34;&gt;Dependency 2: Redis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://redis.io/&#34;&gt;Redis&lt;/a&gt; will be used for storing workloads, created by the server, that will run on a &lt;a href=&#34;https://go-vela.github.io/docs/docs/administration/worker/&#34;&gt;worker&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can refer to &lt;a href=&#34;https://redis.io/topics/quickstart/&#34;&gt;Redis&amp;rsquo;s official documentation&lt;/a&gt; on installing and configuring the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;// TODO: more dependencies we need to cover?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This section provides an example of installing the server with Docker that connects to GitHub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This example only shows a subset of all possible configuration options.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;step-1-download-the-image&#34;&gt;Step 1: Download the Image&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Download the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.docker.com/get-started/overview/#images&#34;&gt;Docker image&lt;/a&gt; for the Vela server from &lt;a href=&#34;https://hub.docker.com/&#34;&gt;DockerHub&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can use the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/commandline/pull/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;docker pull&lt;/code&gt; command&lt;/a&gt; to download the image:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;$ docker pull target/vela-server:latest
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-primary&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&#34;alert-heading&#34;&gt;Note:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;latest&lt;/code&gt; tag will ensure you install the most-recent version of the Vela server.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To see the full list of available versions, please refer to &lt;a href=&#34;https://hub.docker.com/r/target/vela-server&#34;&gt;the official registry&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;step-2-create-an-encryption-key&#34;&gt;Step 2: Create an Encryption Key&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create an &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advanced_Encryption_Standard&#34;&gt;Advanced Encryption Standard (AES)&lt;/a&gt; key used for encrypting sensitive data at rest in the database.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can use the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.openssl.org/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;openssl&lt;/code&gt; command&lt;/a&gt; to generate the AES key:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;$ openssl aes-128-cbc -k secret -P -md sha1
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-primary&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&#34;alert-heading&#34;&gt;Note:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This command will output multiple key/value pairs for the AES key.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The specific value we need from the output is the line with &lt;code&gt;key&lt;/code&gt; in it (i.e. &lt;code&gt;key=&amp;lt;value&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;step-3-create-a-shared-secret&#34;&gt;Step 3: Create a Shared Secret&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a shared secret used for authenticating communication between workers and the server.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can use the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.openssl.org/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;openssl&lt;/code&gt; command&lt;/a&gt; to generate the shared secret:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;$ openssl rand -hex &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0000cf;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;16&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;step-4-create-an-oauth-application&#34;&gt;Step 4: Create an OAuth Application&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.github.com/developers/apps/building-oauth-apps/creating-an-oauth-app&#34;&gt;GitHub OAuth application&lt;/a&gt; used for authentication and authorization with GitHub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://go-vela.github.io/docs/docs/administration/server/github_oauth.png&#34; alt=&#34;OAuth Application&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-secondary&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&#34;alert-heading&#34;&gt;Warning:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;Homepage URL&lt;/code&gt; should match the &lt;code&gt;VELA_ADDR&lt;/code&gt; environment variable below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;Authorization callback URL&lt;/code&gt; should match &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;VELA_ADDR&amp;gt;/authenticate&lt;/code&gt; from the environment variable below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;step-5-start-the-server&#34;&gt;Step 5: Start the Server&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start the Vela server as a &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.docker.com/get-started/overview/#containers&#34;&gt;Docker container&lt;/a&gt; that is configured via environment variables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can use the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/commandline/run/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;docker run&lt;/code&gt; command&lt;/a&gt; to start the server:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;$ docker run &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --detach&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87&#34;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --env&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;VELA_ADDR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;https://vela.company.com &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --env&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;VELA_DATABASE_ENCRYPTION_KEY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;encryption-key&amp;gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --env&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;VELA_QUEUE_DRIVER&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;redis &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --env&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;VELA_QUEUE_ADDR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;redis://&amp;lt;password&amp;gt;@&amp;lt;hostname&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;database&amp;gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --env&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;VELA_PORT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0000cf;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;443&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --env&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;VELA_SECRET&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;shared-secret&amp;gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --env&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;VELA_SCM_CLIENT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;oauth-client-id&amp;gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --env&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;VELA_SCM_SECRET&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;oauth-client-secret&amp;gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --name&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;server &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --publish&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;80:80 &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --publish&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;443:443 &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --restart&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;always &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  target/vela-server:latest
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-primary&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&#34;alert-heading&#34;&gt;Note:&lt;/h4&gt;
For a full list of configuration options, please see the &lt;a href=&#34;https://go-vela.github.io/docs/docs/administration/server/reference/&#34;&gt;server reference&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;step-6-verify-the-server-logs&#34;&gt;Step 6: Verify the Server Logs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure the server started up successfully and is running as expected by viewing the logs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can use the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/commandline/logs/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;docker logs&lt;/code&gt; command&lt;/a&gt; to inspect the logs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;$ docker logs server
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;step-7-install-workers&#34;&gt;Step 7: Install Workers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After the server is up and running, you need to install workers to run workloads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to &lt;a href=&#34;https://go-vela.github.io/docs/docs/administration/worker/&#34;&gt;the worker installation docs&lt;/a&gt; for more information.&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
